      <body>OK, I'm sure your busy, but it would help if you added a small comment as to *why* it's invalid.  The docs *are* in UTF-8 and api.rubyonrails.org *is* setting the meta tag to iso-8859-1.  And this *is* causing an issue with a few UTF-8 characters that are in the documents.  There are other bugs on this tracker for api.rubyonrails.org, so I presume it's OK to have more?

From the site:
&quot;Welcome aboard: You&#226;&#8364;&#8482;re riding the Rails!&quot;
meta http-equiv=&quot;Content-Type&quot; content=&quot;text/html; charset=iso-8859-1&quot;</body>
      <body-html>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;
OK, I'm sure your busy, but it would help if you added a small comment as to &lt;strong&gt;why&lt;/strong&gt; it's invalid.  The docs &lt;strong&gt;are&lt;/strong&gt; in UTF-8 and api.rubyonrails.org &lt;strong&gt;is&lt;/strong&gt; setting the meta tag to iso-8859-1.  And this &lt;strong&gt;is&lt;/strong&gt; causing an issue with a few UTF-8 characters that are in the documents.  There are other bugs on this tracker for api.rubyonrails.org, so I presume it's OK to have more?
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;
From the site:
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;
&quot;Welcome aboard: You&#226;&#8364;&#8482;re riding the Rails!&quot;
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;
